{{Infobox journal | title = Alabama Civil Rights & Civil Liberties Law Review | cover = | discipline = [[Law review]] | abbreviation = Ala. Civ. Rights Civ. Lib. Law Rev. | bluebook = Ala. C.R. & C.L. L. Rev | publisher = [[University of Alabama School of Law]] | country = [[United States]] | frequency = Biannually | history = 2009-present | website = http://www.law.ua.edu/acrcl | ISSN = 2160-9993 }} The '''''Alabama Civil Rights & Civil Liberties Law Review''''' is a student-run [[law review]] published by the [[University of Alabama School of Law]].<ref name=about>{{cite web |url=https://www.law.ua.edu/acrcl/about-the-journal/ |title=About the Journal |work= |accessdate=2017-07-01}}</ref> The journal is published two times per year and contains articles, essays, and book reviews concerning [[civil rights]] and [[civil liberties|liberties]].<ref name=submissions>{{cite web |url=https://www.law.ua.edu/acrcl/submissions/ |title='Submissions'' |format= |work= |accessdate=2017-07-01}}</ref>
==History== The journal was established in 2008 to track developments in the vital and interconnected areas of civil rights and civil liberties. Reflecting on the history of the institution and its place in the narrative of the [[civil rights]] movement, their first issue posed a question: "Have we overcome?" This issue featured "Associational Privacy and the First Amendment: NAACP v. Alabama, Privacy and Data Protection" by Anita L. Allen; "Shall We Overcome? 'Post-Racialism' and Inclusion in the 21st Century" by Sheryll Cashin; "Justice Clarence Thomas: The Burning of Civil Rights Bridges" by Judge U.W. Clemon and Stephanie Y. Moore; "The Students at the University of Alabama in 1845 and the Families that Sent Them" by Royal Dumas; and "The Anti-Apartheid Principle in American Property Law" by Joseph Singer. The inaugural issue featured student-written pieces by Karthik Subramanian and Alexander E. Vaughn‚ÄîKarthik's on the Alabama anti-sex toys statute and Alexander's on the standards for plain view searches involving computers.<ref name=Volume1>{{cite web |url=https://www.law.ua.edu/acrcl/archives/volume-1/ |title=Volume 1 |work= |accessdate=2017-07-01}}</ref>
